body:
as mentioned, you need to use the --build_shared_lib build option to build libonnxruntime.so
the other .so files you mentioned are related to execution providers (e.g. cuda execution provider is always built as a shared library and loaded at runtime when a session is created with cuda provider enabled)

> as mentioned, you need to use the --build_shared_lib build option to build libonnxruntime.so
> the other .so files you mentioned are related to execution providers (e.g. cuda execution provider is always built as a shared library and loaded at runtime when a session is created with cuda provider enabled)
